The paper deals with the problem of multi-robot path planning, which is a topic in both robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on optimization and computational complexity suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the use of Pareto fronts and heuristics suggests a connection to multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
